reviews.text: Our family came in to eat dinner we‚Äôve heard amazing things about this place. Me and my daughter got pasta. Our bill ended up being $125 for my husband, my daughter & I. We got desert as well that was good. The food personally was super overpriced in my opinion and had barely any taste super bland overall our waitress was nice but busy doing other things, but still tried to be attentive and apologized. We were sat down quickly atmosphere was Dark there was a few ladies at the bar intoxicated. It‚Äôs more like a bar with additional sitting and a pool table. Looks like a fun place for locals. Felt more like a pizza üçï and beer kind of place but overall good experience food was OK wouldn‚Äôt go back again. We drove from Hudson, Florida to try it.

Me and my spouse stopped in here randomly on the way home Monday. The lady that helped us was very kind and seemed to know everyone. I got the fried calamari and we were shocked at how tender and delicious it was! The sauce, however, I ended up adding salt and CRP. My man got the mussels and they were pretty good but he kept getting shells in bites. I got the calzone as my meal and it was not very good. I could only taste bread and motzerella. Not sure why there was also red sauce in my cheese calzone? My man got the chicken parm and it tasted ok but the chicken was very hard. And it came on about 15 noodles. Their Nutella raspberry cake was pretty yummy tho! I don‚Äôt think we will be going back because it‚Äôs about an hour drive. But not a total disappointment.

Wife and I had a great lunch at this pizza spot! We tried the $25 special: 12" pizza with three toppings, two salads, and a dessert. The pizza was fantastic, the cheese pull alone was enough to make you want to order another pie, but I'd recommend asking for it well done if you like your undercarriage a bit crispier.

All the bread is made in-house (wow is it good), and you can even grab a loaf to take home, which is a nice touch. The atmosphere is a little on the darker side, but they‚Äôve got lamps at the tables that help brighten things up. The menu is huge, so there‚Äôs a ton left for us to try. Next time, I can‚Äôt wait to order the clams with sauce and linguine, it looked incredible.

We look forward to returning!

Noel was a rockstar. Amazing attention to detail and service. I have multiple food allergies and her commitment to take that serious was noticed and appreciated. The food here is always fantastic and the company from the staff is even better. All smiles and It‚Äôs such a relief to find a place I feel safe to eat.

My boyfriend took me out for my birthday and I wanted pizza from somewhere special!  And boy oh boy was my pizza special...the best most flavorful meat lovers ever!!  When our server (  one of the guys daughters üòä) found out it was my birthday she presented me with a baked in the house cannoli for free‚ù§ We can't wait to go back...

He cut the crust off, even though that's our favorite part, it wasn't worth his getting sick. We were going to stay for the entertainment, but it was too warm in the building (77 degrees on the thermostat behind us) no air moving. All of that put a damper on our datenight. A new pizza should have been made.

detailedReviews.text: 1st time trying this restaurant. Gotta say we were not impressed at all. 13 of us there for a friends birthday all at the same table. So it starts with 1 basket of only 4 rolls & 1 plate. Not one pad of butter. Again, 13 of us. We get our drinks relatively quick & then forever to take our food orders. Then quite awhile to actually get our food. 3 or 4 of us got pasta dishes that were supposed to come with garlic bread. Not a garlic bread in sight!
